article.description: — Atin Wright had 16 points as Cal State Northridge narrowly defeated San Diego 56-52 on Sunday.
article.headline: Wright lifts CS Northridge past San Diego 56-52
article.linkText: Wright lifts CS Northridge past San Diego 56-52
article.story: SAN DIEGO -- — Atin Wright had 16 points as Cal State Northridge narrowly defeated San Diego 56-52 on Sunday. Darius Brown II had 12 points for Cal State Northridge (3-3). Onyi Eyisi added eight rebounds. Marcellus Earlington had 20 points and nine rebounds for the Toreros (4-4). Terrell Brown added nine rebounds and three blocks. Jase Townsend, the Toreros' leading scorer entering the contest at 14 points per game, shot only 13% in the game (1 of 8). Joey Calcaterra, who was second on the Toreros in scoring entering the matchup with 12 points per game, was held to four points on 2-of-11 shooting. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
